logs.content:
I don’t have live web access in this chat, so I can’t fetch real-time prices myself. If you share the current BTC-USD and gold spot (XAU-USD) prices you see, I’ll do the comparison instantly. Or, if you enable browsing, I can pull them for you.

How to get the latest prices (USD):
- Bitcoin (BTC): CoinDesk, Coinbase, Binance, or Yahoo Finance (ticker: BTC-USD)
- Gold spot: Kitco, TradingView (symbol: XAUUSD), CME/COMEX quotes, or Yahoo Finance (GC=F futures as a proxy)

What I’ll calculate once we have them:
- BTC-to-gold ratio (ounces per bitcoin) = BTC_price_USD / Gold_price_USD_per_oz
- Gold-to-BTC ratio (bitcoins per ounce) = Gold_price_USD_per_oz / BTC_price_USD

Example with placeholders:
- If BTC = $65,000 and gold = $2,400/oz:
  - 1 BTC buys 65,000 / 2,400 ≈ 27.1 oz of gold
  - 1 oz of gold buys 2,400 / 65,000 ≈ 0.0369 BTC

Send me the two prices you see, and I’ll compute and summarize the comparison.
